metadata.name: LOW
metadata.description:
LOW, it's a visual representation of how burden can hide who we really are.

When I discovered this outtake from a recent portrait shoot I thought of the first time my dad described his depression episodes; "dull like having a thick tarp over your head you can't escape from."

Although a common expression it had helped me for the first time separate him from his illness.  Years later this film negative manifested itself as a reminder.

A reminder to be more compassionate.
